APPENDIX 175

VERBS

Some groups and pairs of homonyms‚ that are produced within the inflec- tion of a verb by a form from one of its systems coinciding with a form from another, are outlined in the Introduction, pp. xxiii, xxiv. These pairs comprise far the greater number of such cases of coincidence. Other pairs that are formed more rarely are entered in the Alphabetical List as far as they occur in actual use. These rarer coinciding forms are likewise found at certain regular places in the verb-inflection, which it may be interesting to specify.
